<br>
<br>
These three words set the standard for the Violent Harvest’s Code of Conduct.  If you keep these three words close to heart, you will go far.  Our reputation as the premier evil roleplaying guild on Brell Serilis wasn’t achieved easily.  It was achieved by adhering to a code of honor.  Our guild’s honor and reputation should be the top priority of every member, regardless of how we might be treated by our peers.<br>
<br>
To that end, here are our rules of conduct.  All Violent Harvest members will comply regardless of race, class, level, or position within our order.  This Code is a guideline on which to base member actions and responses.  It in no way dictates how any member should roleplay their character, only the individual can make that decision, however, our guild has adopted an “evil” nature and its members will be expected to participate as such. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Conduct of a General Nature:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
1.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp EVERYTHING you do is reflected upon your brothers and sisters in the guild. <br>
<br>
2.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Twinking is not condoned.  Each member will be expected to earn his/her own gear within his/her own ability.  An occasional bequeathal of an item is permitted.  It is never appropriate to ask guildmates for items you yourself could not gain.  Organizing a hunt or raid for items closer to your own skill level is far better. <br>
<br>
3.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Be considerate to everyone around you, guildmates and non-guildmates alike.  While we do roleplay evil, we should not be stepping on other peoples’ enjoyment of the game while we do so.  If someone does not want to roleplay, simply stop. <br>
<br>
4.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Death and experience loss is part of the game.  Don't let it adversely affect you and the others around you. <br>
<br>
5.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Do not get involved in excessive shouting or arguments. If you have a disagreement, take it to /tell.  It shows respect to all involved not to air such disagreements in a public way.  Do not spam any communications channel, i.e. Guild chat, /ooc, etc., with inappropriate content such as profanity, selling of items out of /auction, etc. <br>
<br>
6.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Do not intentionally train. Trains do happen, so try to understand that if you are trained on, it could have been an accident.  If, despite your best efforts you do train others, always apologize and seek to help them with corpse recoveries, finding rezzes, and any other way you can. <br>
<br>
7.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Do not steal another's kill.  If you do accidentally kill something that was already engaged by someone else apologize and step away from the kill, allowing them to loot whatever it has. <br>
<br>
8.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Give everyone the benefit of the doubt, and use diplomacy and tact in every situation.  If you are unable to come to an agreement, walk away or consult with a guild officer.  It is NEVER appropriate to post on any public message board (e.g. Rants Board). <br>
<br>
9.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp If someone is harassing you and will not stop after you have asked them to, use the /petition and /report commands.  It is also a good idea to contact an officer, particularly if the problem is coming from another guild member, or a member of another guild. <br>
<br>
10.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Have fun! <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Conduct Specifically for Harvest members:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
1.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Guild members are expected to participate in guild functions as often as possible.  If you will be unable to attend a major event (i.e. Meeting, Guild War) try to contact an officer to explain your absence.  Missing too many functions will result in removal from the guild. <br>
<br>
2.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Members of the Violent Harvest are to work within the structure of our unique situation.  Every member will learn the chain of command and show all due respect to those in stations higher in the guild structure.  Complaints against other members of the Harvest must go through the member’s chain of command. <br>
<br>
3.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Although it is impossible to remain in character all the time due to the constraints built into “this game”, VH members are expected to participate in roleplay whenever the opportunity arises, especially in support of other members of the guild. <br>
